## Time: timestamps, datetimes, durations

- **Be explicit about timezone**:
  - avoid “naive” datetimes for persisted/serialized values
  - prefer **UTC** at rest, convert at the edges (display/UI)
- **Serialize timestamps predictably**:
  - prefer ISO 8601 / RFC 3339 strings (include `Z` or offset)
  - document units when using epoch seconds/milliseconds
- **Parsing**:
  - handle missing/invalid values deliberately (reject vs coerce vs default)
  - log or surface bad formats when data quality matters
- **Durations in config**:
  - prefer a standard format (e.g. ISO 8601 durations like `PT15M`, `P1D`) or clearly documented units
  - validate duration fields at config load time

